benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/availableBasePlans - Retrieve available base plans

covered: Valid Request: Successful retrieval with and without accountId (TC01, TC02) including content-type and status checks.
Empty Response: Explicit scenarios for empty catalog and regression for empty-array responses (TC03, TC14).
Query Parameters: Tests for valid accountId, non-existent accountId, invalid format, and unsupported extra params (TC02, TC04, TC05, TC08).
Authorization: Unauthorized access is tested (TC06) ensuring 401 behavior.
Error Handling: Service-unavailable, timeout, and generic system error scenarios are present (TC07, TC17).
Security: SQL injection and XSS attempts in accountId are tested (TC12, TC13).
Performance & Scalability: Normal and peak-load performance tests are included (TC09, TC10) and large payload handling is addressed (TC11).
Integration/Partial Data: Dependent-service degradation and partial-content handling are covered (TC16).
Backward Compatibility & Accessibility: Backward compatibility and machine-readable JSON/accessibility are included (TC15, TC18).
Response Validation: Tests assert response is JSON array of PlanDetail objects and include schema/required-field checks in success scenarios.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination (page/limit/offset, boundaries, continuation tokens) or behavior with large datasets beyond single full-list responses.
Caching Behavior & Conditional GETs: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control), conditional GETs (If-None-Match/304), or cache invalidation behavior.
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests to verify rate-limiting behavior (429 responses, Retry-After) or client throttling/backoff.
Authorization nuances: Missing tests for authenticated-but-forbidden scenarios (403) or role/permission-based access control.

Header negotiation & content-encoding: No tests for Accept header variants, Accept-Encoding (gzip), or precise Content-Type variants (charset), nor for response header correctness (Content-Length, Vary).

Schema depth/field-level validation: While required fields are mentioned, there are no explicit tests for field formats, value ranges, nested object validation, or sample value checks for PlanDetail properties.
Deterministic ordering & filtering: No tests to validate ordering, sorting, or additional filtering beyond accountId, and no tests for stable pagination ordering.
Rate/Load edge-cases: Missing tests for graceful degradation under sustained high rate (beyond single peak test) and recovery/metrics (e.g., dropped connections).
Error response consistency: No tests to ensure consistent error response schema/fields across different error paths (400 vs 422 vs 503 vs 504).
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include page/limit/offset parameters, boundary conditions (zero, beyond last page), and ensure deterministic ordering across pages; test behavior with continuations/tokens if supported.
Add caching & conditional GET tests: verify ETag and Cache-Control headers, test If-None-Match/304 behavior, and cache invalidation scenarios when catalog changes.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate bursts to verify 429 responses and Retry-After header, and include client backoff/retry behavior tests.
Add authorization/permissions tests: include authenticated-but-forbidden (403) cases, tenant-isolation checks, and role-based access scenarios.
Expand schema validation: add explicit assertions for each PlanDetail field (types, required/optional, allowed values, date formats, numeric ranges) and negative tests for invalid field values.
Header & encoding tests: validate Accept negotiation, gzip/deflate responses, precise Content-Type header values, and presence of useful response headers (Content-Length, Vary).
Add consistency checks for error payloads: standardize and test error response structure and messages across 4xx/5xx cases.
Add more sustained-load and recovery tests: long-duration high-throughput tests and verification of system behavior and metrics during/after load spikes.
Add tests for deterministic ordering and filtering: ensure predictable sort order and tests for additional query filters if introduced.
